<span id="freeTextContainer7201250635926669935">1945 Caldecott Medal Winner<br/><br/>I&apos;m not quite sure how the illustrations in this were done--it looks like ink and water color, but sometimes the illustrator left the ink outlines off of certain objects like the teddy bear, making them appear almost as though they were done in a different type of media. The whole book is in color with lots of yellow tones.<br/><br/>I like the prayer and that along with the illustrations it includes children all over the world. The words are simple. The way the lines of the poem</span>
  <span id="freeText7201250635926669935" style="display:none">1945 Caldecott Medal Winner<br /><br />I'm not quite sure how the illustrations in this were done--it looks like ink and water color, but sometimes the illustrator left the ink outlines off of certain objects like the teddy bear, making them appear almost as though they were done in a different type of media. The whole book is in color with lots of yellow tones.<br /><br />I like the prayer and that along with the illustrations it includes children all over the world. The words are simple. The way the lines of the poem are broken up on each page is sometimes awkward for the rhymes, but it makes sense for the sake of the illustrations.</span>
